hours_since/minutes_since; live SLA in Service Desk; two computed fixes

Closes gap Б7. hours_since(path)/minutes_since(path) join days_since over a
shared elapsed-time helper — the sub-day granularity an SLA timer needs.

The Service Desk pack now has a live SLA: Incident.sla_left is
`sla_policy.resolution_minutes - minutes_since(opened)`, and the operator board
gains a "Просрочка SLA" tile (`where sla_left < 0`). Driven end-to-end by the
dogfood test (a 30-min policy + an incident opened in 2020 → breached → counted).

Two engine bugs surfaced by that dogfood:
- $now defaults landed at the zero time: validateValues built the default
  context without the engine clock, so `default=$now` wrote 0001-01-01 and every
  elapsed-time computed was wrong from creation. The clock now reaches defaults.
- ref-path computed broke on the dot-spacing the DSL tokenizer leaves
  ("sla_policy . resolution_minutes"): the arithmetic evaluator, unlike
  evalWhere, did not collapse it, so a two-hop deref dropped the whole computed.
  evalComputed now normalizes dot-spaces the same way.

Grammar updated with hours_since/minutes_since.
